1
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:05,680
Short and sweet. We come, we bless, we eat, we leave.

2
00:00:05,760 --> 00:00:08,880
Yeah. We don’t waste time at home either.
We bathe the girls, bathe you, and that’s it.

3
00:00:09,680 --> 00:00:12,600
And good night to everyone.
-What happens at night?

4
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:14,640
What... we sleep. What could happen at night?

5
00:00:16,239 --> 00:00:19,800
Don’t tell her about the babysitter.
-Why are you saying that in Hebrew?

6
00:00:19,880 --> 00:00:21,920
Because she knows the word in English.

7
00:00:22,720 --> 00:00:25,400
Ah... yeah, yeah, yeah—

8
00:00:25,480 --> 00:00:26,680
We’re going out tonight.

9
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:30,080
And it’s really important for our "togetherness."
-Of course.

10
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:32,240
So don’t tell her about the babysitter.

11
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:35,400
Of course I won’t tell her.
What, do you think I’m crazy?

12
00:00:37,160 --> 00:00:39,840
I care about it too... it’s important to me.

13
00:00:40,840 --> 00:00:43,200
I’ve been waiting for this too.

14
00:00:43,280 --> 00:00:44,720
Wow...
-Wow.

15
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:50,240
So what’s his "bet"?

16
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:52,240
Do you really want me to tell you?

17
00:00:53,480 --> 00:00:57,200
Yes, please.
-If you’re asking so nicely.

18
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,760
What do you think about this:

19
00:01:00,760 --> 00:01:04,680
You, me, music,

20
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:10,280
grapefruit vodka...
How do you say "אשכוליות" in English?

21
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:12,880
"Grapefruit."
-Grapefruit.

22
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:18,800
Do you think she understands?
-Yeah.

23
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:22,720
Great, babe. Great.

24
00:01:28,520 --> 00:01:30,480
Look at me, look at me and...

25
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:42,280
Shabbat shalom.
-Shabbat shalom.

26
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:45,920
Shabbat shalom.

27
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:46,840
Shabbat shalom.

28
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:50,960
Pinchas, what’s up, how are you?
-Okay.

29
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:53,280
We can’t stay long today.
-Yeah.

30
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:55,600
I hope Adam and Itamar get here soon.
-What happened?

31
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:58,520
I have a date.
-Something special?

32
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:01,480
The date is with her.
-Oh, that’s so nice.

33
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:03,320
It’s really important for the relationship.

34
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:06,040
Right. Don’t let it happen to you like it did to Itamar and Smadar.

35
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:09,000
I’ll go to the kitchen and speed things up for you.

36
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:10,280
I’ll help you with the schnitzels.

37
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:12,680
So where are you going to strengthen the relationship?

38
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:15,680
Me, wait a second. It’s from the babysitter.
-I’m sure she won’t bail.

39
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:18,240
No. Why would she bail?
-What, did she bail?

40
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:23,200
No, she didn’t bail. She just said
she’ll be late because her grandma is in the hospital.

41
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,440
Didn’t bail.

42
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:29,480
Good you came. I wasn’t comfortable around Shabi.

43
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:33,440
So what? You guys strengthening?
-What?

44
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:36,000
The relationship. Did she say anything?

45
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:37,560
No, why would she say anything? Everything’s fine.

46
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:41,120
Are you sure?
-Yeah. It’s just, Shabi and I haven’t gone out in a long time,

47
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:44,400
you know, the kids and all...
-The kids are not an excuse.

48
00:02:44,480 --> 00:02:47,360
I never let the kids
get in the way of me and Pinchas.

49
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:49,840
Mom, mom! I know—I know—

50
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:53,400
Everything’s great. We’re having fun,
happy, everything... everything’s great.

51
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:56,040
Great. Awesome. It’s good you’re still in the game.

52
00:02:56,720 --> 00:03:00,080
You know, marriage, you open the door for them,

53
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:03,080
they escape through the window.
-Yeah.

54
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,200
I think the schnitzels escaped through the window.

55
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:11,600
It’s good to break the routine. You never know

56
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:14,880
where the gray monster of boredom is hiding.

57
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:16,800
Speaking of hiding: where are the schnitzels?

58
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:19,840
Nothing, nothing on you
-Nothing...

59
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:23,120
Very healthy. Yeah. But tofu.

60
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:27,360
I wanted to break the routine, so you wouldn’t escape through the window.

61
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:32,600
How old was she, Grandma?
-Why was she? She's not dead.

62
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:34,880
Why would she die? She's just in the hospital.

63
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:36,320
Ooooh
'Ooooh

64
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:37,240
Ova.

65
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:40,040
Hey, glad you came. It's already a quarter past.
-What did we do to her?

66
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:42,600
Shani's anxious to work on the relationship.
-Did something happen?

67
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:46,760
Me! Shai and I are going out. Just kidding.
-It's really not just kidding, babe.

68
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:48,640
It's really not just kidding. It's super important for the relationship.

69
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:51,320
Me! Itamar insists, even if the guy's not really in the mood,

70
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:55,800
And even if we went out yesterday,
to clear our heads, work on the "togetherness,"

71
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:57,360
and most importantly, to...

72
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:00,800
Dance at least three or four times a week.

73
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:04,360
Good for you.
-Hey, if Itamar was like that,

74
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:07,560
three or four times with Smadar, everything...
-Come on, what's wrong with you?

75
00:04:07,760 --> 00:04:10,640
What? What happened to Itamar?
-No, he has some issue with...

76
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:14,760
Never mind. Where did you think of going?
-It's not really important, what.

77
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:17,079
Do you know how long it's been since I
went to a good movie?

78
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:19,920
Want to come with us to "Jabaki"?
-No, I don't think so.

79
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:22,720
Never mind. The main thing is to work on your relationship,

80
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:26,320
and I'm sure the babysitter won't bail.
-Why would she bail?

81
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:29,360
Is that her?
-The babysitter?

82
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:31,240
Bailed?
-Sit down, can you wait a sec?

83
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:32,160
Boy
Sit down

84
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:37,160
It's great they're working on their relationship.
-Their relationship is just fine.

85
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:41,400
No, of course.
-Okay, excuse me for a sec.

86
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:45,760
What happened to him?
-His red light came back.

87
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:56,640
There's a problem.
-How do you know?

88
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:58,680
How do I know? There are no schnitzels.
-What?

89
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:02,280
No schnitzels, no shlaykler, no schweitz.
-Shai, what are you talking about?

90
00:05:02,520 --> 00:05:05,280
About the food my mom made,
if you can even call it food.

91
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:07,160
Okay, drop it. There's a bigger problem.

92
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:09,440
They have an issue with the babysitter.
-She doesn't have shlaykler?

93
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:11,560
No, she bailed on them. Her grandma passed away.

94
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:14,440
Is that a reason to bail?
-I don't know. Your dad gave them the evil eye.

95
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:18,360
And you know who can fix this? Your mom.
-What do you mean?

96
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:21,160
I mean your mom can watch the girls for us,
and you can go ask her.

97
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:23,840
No, sit down, sit down,
you're just upset about your grandma.

98
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:26,280
No, I'm not upset.
I'm completely serious. Why can only my mom

99
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:28,800
watch the kids?
Your mom can babysit sometimes too.

100
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:31,200
Fine, I just think
it's not a good time to ask her

101
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:33,840
because it stresses her out that the kids are little.
-What little?

102
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:35,760
The kids are already big. Enough with the excuse.

103
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:38,240
It's not an excuse. I'm telling you, something happened.
-What happened?

104
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:40,240
Suddenly you don't have schnitzels?
-There's dandelion.

105
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:45,800
Do you even know what dandelion looks like?
-No. But I know what lamb's lettuce looks like.

106
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:49,520
Go talk to your mom. Now.

107
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:54,200
Hey, Riki, Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

108
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:57,320
What, is this millet? Wow, I'm shocked.

109
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:02,720
What? You made lupin?
-I decided to try. I'm almost done.

110
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:05,400
What, I'll help you, wow, that's amazing.

111
00:06:05,880 --> 00:06:07,640
No way. You made maash?

112
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:12,040
Who has the energy for shlaykler again?
-What, Riki, is this for me?

113
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:15,600
You made vegetarian for me?
How sweet, you didn't have to.

114
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:19,520
Wow, this is great. I hope
you soaked the lupin enough in water.

115
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:22,160
Yeah.
-It's a bit hard to soften them...

116
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:23,680
True.
-But it's worth the effort.

117
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:28,320
Kind of like Shani. You know
they've started working on their relationship.

118
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:32,200
Yeah, I've been wanting to tell her for a while
that she's been neglecting herself

119
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:34,760
lately.
-True. But it's also kids and all, you know.

120
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:36,800
But kids are not an excuse.
-Yeah.

121
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:39,920
You know, I'm so happy
that we can talk like this.

122
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,600
Wow, me too, Riki.
-You know you're my favorite bride.

123
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:46,120
No, I'm dying. You too...

124
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:49,920
Wow, you're stunning! Wow.

125
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:52,240
Where's Mom?
-In the kitchen.

126
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:56,600
You know, Dad, what...

127
00:06:56,680 --> 00:07:00,240
All week the girls won't stop talking about you.

128
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,840
"Grandpa, Grandpa."
-Yes.

129
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,040
So Grandma passed away?

130
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,240
Passed away.
-Passed away.

131
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:06,920
So what do you say? Help your son with the girls.

132
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:09,400
It's so important for his relationship.
-I get you,

133
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:13,200
I really get you, but you
have to ask Mom about these things.

134
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,680
It's important for my relationship.

135
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:18,520
I don't know if it's a fungus
or a rash, but this redness

136
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:21,320
is killing me... from what.
-Funny.

137
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:25,360
You think it's funny that I'm in pain?
-No, I just...

138
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:30,440
The girls won't stop talking about you all week.
"Uncle Itamar, Uncle Itamar..."

139
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:32,160
"Itamar, Itamar."
-Did she bail?

140
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,120
Passed away.

141
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:36,920
My condolences.
-So participate in the effort too.

142
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:40,960
Shai, it's not me, it's Michal.
She needs to deal with my monsters anyway,

143
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:43,680
so now she has to handle your... princesses?

144
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,640
You understand me, Shani?
-Yeah, yeah. Of course.

145
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:47,200
I'm red.
-So...

146
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:50,440
So... your mom is in the kitchen, by the chard.

147
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:57,120
Oh, do me a favor, Itamar.

148
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,880
Yummy.
-Bless you.

149
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,280
No, that's beans.

150
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:07,560
You have to mix it with the millet.
It gives it this aroma...

151
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:11,040
They'll love it.
-Michal, Itamar needs you. He's red.

152
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:13,760
He can be such a kid sometimes,
and I have a ton of natural ointments,

153
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:15,920
but he doesn't want to apply them. Ugh.

154
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:22,920
It smells really... what is it?
-Spelt pilaf.

155
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:28,800
It looks, looks great.
Mom, if you don't mind me asking...

156
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:31,920
Shai, I'm really sorry,
there are no schnitzels today, okay?

157
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:36,000
You'll live with it. Nothing bad will happen.
-No, come on, that's not what I wanted.

158
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:40,000
The... cup... the... looks great. It's nutritious.

159
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:42,919
Now you're making fun of my food?
-No. No.

160
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:44,720
I wanted to ask you for a small favor.

161
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:48,760
The babysitter bailed on my son,
and we really want to go out today.

162
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,480
It's so important for Shani. So I wanted to ask

163
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,520
if you don't mind the girls staying here tonight.

164
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:57,480
I'm sorry, Shai. It's really
not suitable for me. It's really not suitable for me

165
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:59,920
for them to stay here tonight.
-When is it suitable for you?

166
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:03,320
What did you say?
-I'm not saying,

167
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:05,880
but Shani is right.
-Shani.

168
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:10,040
Not Shani. No, me. Me. Me... Mom, look,

169
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:12,000
you never help us with the girls.

170
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:14,600
You helped Itamar when he got divorced. Right?
So why not for my girls?

171
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:17,880
What, do I need to get divorced for that?
I really don't understand you.

172
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:21,920
Once I'm asking you
to do something for me and even then you don't...

173
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:25,280
So that's how you feel?
-Yeah, yeah. Yeah.

174
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:29,240
Okay, so if you really want to know,
and I didn't want to tell you this

175
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:33,320
to avoid worrying you, then I
can't babysit your girls today

176
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:37,360
because yesterday
I had general tests done

177
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:40,920
!the result is crap. Okay?

178
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:43,480
What? So what's wrong with you?

179
00:09:43,560 --> 00:09:48,400
The health fund's website
couldn't believe what I have in my blood.

180
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:52,320
So I'm sorry there are no schnitzels,
but there's healthier food instead.

181
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:55,160
And I can't babysit my girls.

182
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:58,200
So you and Shani can go dance.

183
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:02,480
Luckily, it won't take much longer.

184
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:11,520
Hey, did you talk to her?

185
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,600
I think he asked her.
-I'll handle it.

186
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:27,680
This red is driving me crazy. I don't know
if I suffer more sitting,

187
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:30,320
standing, or walking.
It's just driving me nuts, babe.

188
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:34,720
Enough, I can't take it anymore.
-Babe.

189
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:42,040
Ohh
Ohh

190
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:45,560
Meet Sivan.

191
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,080
Hi.
-Michal.

192
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:49,920
And the uncultured one is my brother, Itamar.
-Nice to meet you.

193
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:52,240
Tell me, are you normal? We saw you.

194
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:55,400
It's fine, I'm used to people like that from work.
-You work at the safari?

195
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:58,960
At the hospital.
-Sivan's an intern.

196
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:04,120
That's how we met. You just came to pick up
my tests and... I'm healthy.

197
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:06,960
More than I can say
about some of my recent dates.

198
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:09,920
What, so you're a doctor?
-Intern.

199
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:12,800
Great, because I have just a little question.
Do you know anything about red?

200
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:22,000
I haven't been "ouch" for a long time,
but you guys don't even notice.

201
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:24,920
Rivka.
-Pinchas, give me five minutes.

202
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:26,560
Riki, come on...

203
00:11:28,680 --> 00:11:30,440
Can't I be a little sad?

204
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:34,920
You can, of course you can,
but maybe now isn't the right time.

205
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:38,480
Oh, really? So when is the right time?
After I die?

206
00:11:39,040 --> 00:11:42,640
Why would you die? Seriously.
We're going to the doctor on Sunday,

207
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:45,080
and he'll tell us what's going on. Okay?
-Yeah. What will he say?

208
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:48,720
You already know, you saw the results.
-Do we understand this?

209
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:51,600
He understands it. Come on Sunday
and he'll tell us everything.

210
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:55,560
Ugh, so unfair. All these years you were sick

211
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:59,120
while I was as healthy as a horse,
and now I'm going to die first

212
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:03,320
and the kids will starve.
-They won't starve.

213
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:06,160
Rivka, who can hate dandelions?

214
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,760
And they don't know what's wrong with her?
-No.

215
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:15,240
What should I do?
-Babe,

216
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:18,040
it'll be okay. We'll get through this together.

217
00:12:18,520 --> 00:12:21,280
And the last thing I did was laugh at her.
-Enough, Shai.

218
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:25,280
You know it's all because of you.
-Enough, babe.

219
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:28,960
It's really good that you talked to her.
-She won't watch the girls. Forget it.

220
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:33,160
I'm not talking about that, Shai. I'm talking
about how good it is that she told you.

221
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:35,040
And now you also need to tell your brothers.

222
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:37,640
